<table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0"><tr><td>
	     <table class="mform"  border="0" cellpadding="1" cellspacing="0" width="100%" >
	     <form action="/cgi-bin/mrate.pl" name="f105517794345888">
	     <tr><td id="headerrow" colspan="2" class="mform" valign="top"><a id="sj" href="/db/item.html?item=11470&amp;mid=105517794345888">The War</a> <a id="fs8" href="/db/item.html?item=11470&amp;mid=105517794345888#post"><img src="/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif" border="0" alt="Reply..." width="17" height="11" /></a>
	     <br clear="all" /><small>Posted @ Mon, Jun 9th 1:39 PM 2003</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform"><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=117002"><span id="Scholar">cannonballdex</span></a><br /><b><span id="Scholar">Scholar</span></b><br /><span id="notbold">18 posts<br /><span id="notbold">Score</span>: Default [2.00]</td><td valign=top class="mform" width="100%"><p>This war starts approximatley every 20-30 minutes. You will see a message of mobs scurrying ect. The owlbears march from the owlbear cave to the grimlings in the south as well as march to the sonic wolfs to the northeast. You simply assist whichever mobs you want to win. When one specific group, owlbears, grimlings, or sonic wolfs take over all three camps, then the merchant town by the entrance to vah shir depops of guards and merchants and becomes the mob boss for whichever mob took over the three camps, when you kill this boss, then the whole zone resets back to normal again.</p>&nbsp;<br /><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br />Do I Have Too?</td></tr>
	     <tr><td colspan="2" align="right" class="mform" id="fs8">1 Reply</td></tr>
	     </form></table>
<tr><td colspan="2"><ul>
<table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0"><tr><td>
	     <table class="mform"  border="0" cellpadding="1" cellspacing="0" width="100%" >
	     <form action="/cgi-bin/mrate.pl" name="f105828977142701">
	     <tr><td id="headerrow" colspan="2" class="mform" valign="top"><a id="sj" href="/db/item.html?item=11470&amp;mid=105828977142701">RE: The War</a> <a id="fs8" href="/db/item.html?item=11470&amp;mid=105828977142701#post"><img src="/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif" border="0" alt="Reply..." width="17" height="11" /></a>
	     <br clear="all" /><small>Posted @ Tue, Jul 15th 1:32 PM 2003</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform"><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=156951"><span id="Scholar">Grabble</span></a><br /><b><span id="Scholar">Scholar</span></b><br /><span id="notbold">78 posts<br /><span id="notbold">Score</span>: Default [2.20]</td><td valign=top class="mform" width="100%"><p>A little clarification as certain people seem confused... when you see the zone message describing one side attacking another, for example the Grimlings attacking the Owlbears, two sets of mobs will spawn for the races described.<br/><br/>Using Grimling attacking Owlbears as the example if you stand just outside of the Owlbear caves where there are normally two owlbear guards either side there will now be some perma rooted owlbear defenders (be warned these ones summon so pick them off one by one if you're unsure). <br/><br/>If you wait a couple of minutes you will see a small party of grimlings come down the path and attack these owlbear defenders on the door. (Note: none of the regular owlbears will attack them before they get to the cave entrance). <br/><br/>If you choose to help the grimlings win, then kill off all but one of the owlbear defenders before the grimlings arrive and allow the grimling raiding party to kill the last one. <br/><br/>Shortly after the grimlings kill the last owlbear defender they will head into the cave and eventually despawn and you will see a zone message that the Grimlings were victorious. <br/><br/>Shortly after the owlbears will despawn and be replaced by Grimlings. Repeat the same for the sonic wolves to replace them with Grimlings and you will spawn the Boss Grimling mob at the outpost just outside Shar Vahl. Be warned, he doesnt stay up long, so when you've populated the zone with only one race in all three areas get over to the outpost quickly.<br/><br/>You can obviously influence who wins the war, be it Grimling, Owlbear or Sonic Wolf and you get a different boss mob for each of the different races. Each of which drops different gear.</p>&nbsp;<br /><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br />Grabble<br/>Ogre Shaman<br/>Antonious Bayle</td></tr>
