	     <tr><td id="headerrow" colspan="2" class="mform" valign="top"><a id="sj" href="/db/item.html?item=11470&amp;mid=106062472592124">RE: The War</a> <a id="fs8" href="/db/item.html?item=11470&amp;mid=106062472592124#post"><img src="/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif" border="0" alt="Reply..." width="17" height="11" /></a>
	     <br clear="all" /><small>Posted @ Mon, Aug 11th 2:00 PM 2003</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform"><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=215976"><span id=" ">NatueskStormwalker</span></a><br /><span id="notbold">23 posts<br /><span id="notbold">Score</span>: Decent [2.66]</td><td valign=top class="mform" width="100%"><p>Ok I've seen several occasions in posts where players have said:<br/><br/> <BLOCKQUOTE><b id=fs8>Quote:</b><hr size=1>If you choose to help the grimlings win, then kill off <b>all but one of</b> the owlbear defenders before the grimlings arrive <b>and allow the grimling raiding party to kill the last one</b>. <br/><hr size=1></BLOCKQUOTE><br/><br/>Ok....this is BS, see the bold sections above??? Remove those and this is correct. Just nuke/slay the everliving crap out of these suckers (defenders/invaders etc) for whichever side you want to lose and they will. Kill the spawns outside of the caves if you want the invading faction to win. If its in the south, kill the (resident/non-resident) mobs for them to win. <b> DO NOT WAIT FOR THE INVADERS TO ARRIVE!!! </b></p>&nbsp;<br /><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br />Natuesk Stormwalker<br/><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=568183" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=568183</a></td></tr>
